The paper deals with the complexity of a graph problem, specifically the Path Avoiding Forbidden Pairs (PAFP) problem, which involves directed acyclic graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the study of different special cases of the PAFP problem, which could fall under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of boolean matrices, which could suggest a connection to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
